data.content:
noun
plural pike or pikes
[count] :a large fish that lives in rivers and lakes and that has a long body and sharp teeth - compare 2pike 3pike
noun
plural pikes
[count] US informal :a road that people must pay to use :turnpike
usually used with the
There might be a lot of traffic on the pike. - compare 1pike 3pike
down the pike
US informal
in the future
Today's technology is only a hint at what's down the pike. [=down the road]
come down the pike :to happen or appear
He is the greatest boxer to come down the pike [=come along] in years.
A chance like this doesn't come down the pike every day.
noun
plural pikes
[count] :a long wooden pole with a steel point that was used in the past as a weapon - compare 1pike 2pike
